+    "**Cessna 172 Skyhawk** — the textbook example of a conventional circular-section fuselage on a\n",
+    "high-wing general aviation aircraft. *Photo: Md Shaifuzzaman — [CC BY-SA 4.0](https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Cessna%20172%20Skyhawk%2C%20S2-AFH.jpg), Wikimedia Commons.*\n",
+    "```\n",
+    "\n",
+    "Every pressurised transport — from the Douglas DC-3 onward — uses a circular or near-circular\n",
+    "fuselage cross-section for one simple reason: a pressure vessel cycling through 8–9 psi\n",
+    "differential pressure distributes hoop stress uniformly only in a circle {cite}`raymer2018`.\n",
+    "An oval is a compromise: more headroom without a full double-bubble (as in the 787), but with\n",
+    "heavier local reinforcement wherever the curvature changes.\n",
+    "\n",
+    "**Full-scale advantages.** Structurally efficient under pressurisation. The frame-and-stringer\n",
+    "semi-monocoque construction standard since the 1950s achieves an excellent strength-to-weight\n",
+    "ratio. Circular frames integrate cleanly with circular sections, simplifying jig and tooling\n",
+    "design for high-rate production.\n",
+    "\n",
+    "**Full-scale disadvantages.** A circular fuselage has high wetted area for a given usable\n",
+    "internal volume. On a typical airliner the fuselage contributes roughly 30–40% of total zero-lift\n",
+    "drag. There is also a fundamental conflict between the ideal aerodynamic shape (fineness ratio\n",
+    "~10:1) and the ideal structural shape (short, thick cylinder) — airliners sit in the middle and\n",
+    "pay a penalty in both.\n",
+    "\n",
+    "**RC advantages.** Circular fibreglass or carbon tube fuselages are light, stiff, and easy to\n",
+    "source. They transmit torque well, which matters for models landing in unusual attitudes. Most\n",
+    "sport and scale RC models use formed fibreglass fuselages for this reason.\n",
+    "\n",
+    "**RC disadvantages.** Internal access is poor once closed. Any component buried behind the wing\n",
+    "former requires significant disassembly. Belly hatches weaken the structure at the highest bending\n",
+    "moment location unless carefully reinforced.\n"
    ]
