--- a/release_patch.patch
+++ /dev/null
@@ -1,4863 +0,0 @@
-From 60a1c4add33d589950eed0c86a55b1213da928ac Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
-From: Benny Godwin <bennygodwin03@gmail.com>
-Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 17:58:02 -0500
-Subject: [PATCH] Add Chapter 2 (all 7 notebooks) and Section 5.1 fixed-wing
- configurations
-MIME-Version: 1.0
-Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
-Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
-
-Chapter 2 — Stakeholders, Requirements & Systems Engineering:
-- 2.1 Stakeholder Identification & Analysis (power-interest matrix, vehicle type radar chart)
-- 2.2 Needs, Goals & Objectives (requirements hierarchy pyramid, TLAR bar chart)
-- 2.3 Requirements Engineering (V-model diagram, RTM heatmap)
-- 2.4 Mission Profiles (3-panel profile plots, payload-range diagram)
-- 2.5 Design Drivers & Figures of Merit (weighted decision matrix, Pareto front)
-- 2.6 The Systems Engineering Process (IPT org chart, lifecycle Gantt with maturity curves)
-- 2.7 The Design Review Cycle (cost-of-change bar chart, design review timeline)
-
-Section 5.1 — Fixed-Wing Aircraft Configurations:
-- Fuselage layouts: conventional, pod-and-boom, twin fuselage, slab-sided
-- Wing position: high, shoulder, mid, low with full-scale and RC pros/cons separately
