-+  {
-+   "cell_type": "markdown",
-+   "id": "md-s02-05-b",
-+   "metadata": {},
-+   "source": [
-+    "*Figure 1 — A weighted decision matrix comparing four UAV concepts across five\n",
-+    "criteria. The colour intensity in the left panel indicates raw score (darker blue =\n",
-+    "higher score). The bar chart on the right shows the weighted total. Concept B\n",
-+    "(conventional tail-aft layout) leads on maintenance simplicity and unit cost; Concept\n",
-+    "A (flying wing) leads on endurance. The winning score on the weighted total reflects\n",
-+    "the programme's priority ordering — endurance was assigned the highest weight (30%).\n",
-+    "Constructed from the methodology in {cite}`ullman2009`.*\n",
-+    "\n",
-+    "## Pareto Fronts and Trade Studies\n",
-+    "\n",
-+    "Many design problems involve figures of merit that cannot be simultaneously maximised.\n",
-+    "Increasing range requires more fuel, which increases weight, which increases fuel\n",
-+    "burn — the trade space is genuinely multidimensional and the best solution depends\n",
-+    "on which FOM the operator values most.\n",
-+    "\n",
-+    "A Pareto front is the boundary of the non-dominated solution space: the set of\n",
-+    "designs for which no other design achieves a better value on one FOM without being\n",
-+    "worse on another. Designs on the Pareto front represent genuine trade-offs. Designs\n",
-+    "inside the front — in the dominated region — are unambiguously inferior, because\n",
-+    "another design achieves better performance on both FOMs simultaneously, and there is\n",
-+    "no engineering reason to prefer the dominated design.\n",
-+    "\n",
-+    "Trade studies in early conceptual design use this framework. A parametric study\n",
-+    "varies a design parameter — wing loading, aspect ratio, engine bypass ratio, payload\n",
-+    "fraction — and plots the resulting designs in the FOM space. The Pareto front emerges\n",
-+    "from the parametric sweep, and the design team identifies which region of the front\n",
-+    "satisfies the priority ordering established in the requirements process.\n",
-+    "\n",
-+    "Figure 2 shows a representative Pareto front for a regional turboprop design,\n",
-+    "plotting seat-mile cost against range with full payload. Different wing loading\n",
-+    "assumptions produce the family of designs shown.\n"
-+   ]
-+  },
-+  {
-+   "cell_type": "code",
-+   "execution_count": null,
-+   "id": "code-s02-05-fig2",
-+   "metadata": {},
-+   "outputs": [],
-+   "source": [
-+    "import matplotlib as mpl\n",
-+    "mpl.rcParams.update({\n",
-+    "    'figure.facecolor': 'none', 'axes.facecolor': 'none',\n",
-+    "    'savefig.facecolor': 'none', 'savefig.transparent': True,\n",
-+    "    'axes.edgecolor': '#888888', 'axes.labelcolor': '#cccccc',\n",
-+    "    'text.color': '#cccccc', 'xtick.color': '#cccccc', 'ytick.color': '#cccccc',\n",
-+    "    'grid.color': '#555555', 'font.size': 14, 'axes.titlesize': 16,\n",
-+    "    'axes.labelsize': 14, 'xtick.labelsize': 13, 'ytick.labelsize': 13,\n",
-+    "    'legend.fontsize': 13, 'legend.title_fontsize': 13,\n",
-+    "    'figure.titlesize': 16, 'lines.linewidth': 2.0,\n",
-+    "})\n",
-+    "OKI = ['#0072B2','#D55E00','#009E73','#E69F00','#56B4E9','#CC79A7','#F0E442','#333333']\n",
-+    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
-+    "import matplotlib.patches as mpatches\n",
-+    "import numpy as np\n",
-+    "\n",
-+    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
-+    "n = 80\n",
-+    "# Wing loading sweep: higher WL -> higher range (cruise efficiency gain)\n",
-+    "# but also higher cost (heavier structure, more complex systems).\n",
-+    "# This creates a genuine Pareto trade-off: more range costs more.\n",
-+    "WL       = np.linspace(280, 620, n)\n",
-+    "range_km = 1350 + 1.3*(WL - 280) + np.random.normal(0, 30, n)\n",
-+    "smc      = 0.033 + 0.00015*(WL - 280) + np.random.normal(0, 0.0022, n)\n",
-+    "\n",
-+    "# Pareto front: maximise range, minimise smc.\n",
-+    "# Point j dominates i if j has >= range AND <= smc (at least one strict).\n",
-+    "pareto_mask = np.ones(n, dtype=bool)\n",
-+    "for i in range(n):\n",
-+    "    for j in range(n):\n",
-+    "        if i == j:\n",
-+    "            continue\n",
-+    "        if range_km[j] >= range_km[i] and smc[j] <= smc[i]:\n",
-+    "            if range_km[j] > range_km[i] or smc[j] < smc[i]:\n",
