-+   "source": [
-+    "*Figure 2 — A Pareto front for a regional turboprop design, generated by a\n",
-+    "parametric sweep of wing loading. Blue points on the Pareto front represent\n",
-+    "non-dominated designs — genuine trade-offs between seat-mile cost and range. Grey\n",
-+    "points in the dominated region are strictly inferior: a Pareto-front design achieves\n",
-+    "better performance on both FOMs simultaneously. The design team's task is to select\n",
-+    "the point on the Pareto front that best satisfies the programme's priority ordering.\n",
-+    "Methodology from {cite}`torenbeek2013` and {cite}`raymer2018`; numerical values are\n",
-+    "illustrative.*\n",
-+    "\n",
-+    "## How Trade Studies Feed Back into Requirements\n",
-+    "\n",
-+    "A well-structured trade study does more than select a design concept — it informs\n",
-+    "the requirements. If the Pareto analysis shows that achieving the range objective\n",
-+    "requires a wing loading that raises seat-mile cost beyond the operator's economic\n",
-+    "threshold, the design team has identified a requirements conflict. The resolution\n",
-+    "must come from the customer: either relax the range objective, accept the higher\n",
-+    "operating cost, or invest in technology that moves the Pareto front outward.\n",
-+    "\n",
-+    "This is the design process working as intended. Trade studies expose the cost of\n",
-+    "requirements, and that cost is expressed in terms the operator can evaluate — not\n",
-+    "abstract engineering metrics, but fuel burn, seat-mile cost, and acquisition price.\n",
-+    "The requirements that survive this scrutiny are the ones the customer is actually\n",
-+    "willing to pay for. The requirements that do not survive it should be relaxed, not\n",
-+    "carried forward into preliminary design as unresolved constraints.\n",
-+    "\n",
-+    "```{tip}\n",
-+    "When presenting a trade study, always show the dominated region alongside the\n",
-+    "Pareto front. If all the designs shown are on the front, the audience cannot see\n",
-+    "how much of the design space is suboptimal or how far the front is from the nearest\n",
-+    "infeasible region. The dominated points are the context that makes the front\n",
-+    "meaningful.\n",
-+    "```\n",
-+    "\n",
-+    "```{seealso}\n",
-+    "Torenbeek Chapter 2 provides a systematic treatment of aircraft performance figures\n",
-+    "of merit and their relationship to conceptual design sizing, with particular depth on\n",
-+    "civil transport aircraft economics: {cite}`torenbeek2013`.\n",
-+    "\n",
-+    "Ullman's *Mechanical Design Process* covers weighted decision matrices and multi-\n",
-+    "criteria decision analysis in detail: {cite}`ullman2009`.\n",
-+    "\n",
-+    "The NASA Systems Engineering Handbook Section 6 covers trade study methodology and\n",
-+    "the use of design of experiments (DoE) for parametric design space exploration:\n",
-+    "{cite}`nasa2017seh`.\n",
-+    "```\n",
-+    "\n",
-+    "```{bibliography}\n",
-+    ":filter: docname in docnames\n",
-+    "```\n"
